  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The main objective of the study is to evaluate ginger efficacy as an prophylactic treatment
      of migraine.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Patients with the diagnosis of migraine according to the IHS criteria will receive capsules
      of 200 mg of ginger extract (5% active ingredient) or placebo (cellulose) to be taken three
      times a day for 12 weeks.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
